                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 81.2.00/9952.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                            Juárez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No reliable news from Chihuahua City, but the general impression is that it will
                    fall into the hands of the rebels without battle.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
